caption: Beautiful jardin/parc just across the street Rue Louis Boilly and just nearby Musee Marmottan Monet. I‚Äôm just taking rest and drinking rest my feet after long walks and enjoying the museum then sitting on the bench here. There‚Äôs also little soccer or futsal field for kiddos playing around.

Nice open spaces. It has 2 playground areas for children, separated by a street with cars passing by, so you have to choose. It also has an outdoors fitness area for adults. Passing cars across the middle keep it from being truly quiet. There is puppet theatre with sessions at 3:15pm and 4:15pm for EU3.50. And there are ponies available for rides in the afternoon.
Great place to hang out with the kids, have a picnic or just workout. Although it's open 24/7, it's safe to bring kids and toddlers.
Very family friendly park with lots of room to picnic, lay in the grass, take a walk. Very nice atmosphere.  Kiosk on weekends for snacks and drinks.

A delicious park for picnicking, playing ball with children, resting under a tree‚Ä¶ And it offers a free sparkling water fountain! Not far from Trocadero, in a more residential area, a very beautiful one!

Jardin du Ranelagh is a peaceful oasis, just a three minute walk from La Muette stop on Line 9 of the Paris Metro. People have picnics here and there are well resourced children's playgrounds. Across the road is Marmottan Museum.
Nice park, quite quiet. Lots of benches, an outdoor gym and play park. Lots of shade
Lovely, fun playground!

It's a good place to go with the kids, it has two different playgrounds one of them has sand all over the ground, outside "gym", ping-pong, small football field (soccer), closed street for bikes, and places to do picnic.
A very nice, clean, open square for everyone to enjoy. A lot of teenagers were there playing football and other sports. I just sat to rest a little bit and look and enjoy the clear wind.

Very well laid out park in ex pat neighborhood.  Playground for all ages, some equipment a bit adventurous for American children but plenty to choose from.  Swings are a Euro for five minutes.  Sand lot available, good idea to bring beach toys for kids.

Great play area for smaller and bigger kids, available toilets and not much traffic! It‚Äôs also close to a couple nice restaurants and boulangeries so it‚Äôs pretty much all you need! A good address to have in mind when looking for a local playground that doesn‚Äôt include one very sad tiny slide and a half in a gated square üòÅ parents will know what I mean!
Small park but nice. Good place for relaxation
it's my neighborhood park vast area and very accessible
It's already hot in Paris and a lot of kids love to play here..
Nice park! 2 small playgrounds for children, a dedicated fitness area, an off leash dog area and lots of other greenspace for activities.  Playgrounds are a bit small for my 9 year old.

A well-kept and nice garden.  I wouldn't go to hang out in the garden only and the payment doesn't justify it - 7‚Ç¨ per person.  The facilities are suitable for family fun with children up to 12 years old.

Nice park. There are ponies to ride for the children and several playgrounds to choose from. There's a little play area for football/soccer. There's also a little ride for the little ones, plenty of open space for picnics and playing.  It can be quite crowded on beautiful days at peak hours.
I love Jean de la fontaine, nice statue.... the area is cool for hang out with friends or ride bike around

Nice quiet park during the week and slightly more packed during the weekend. It‚Äôs a great place to relax and host some outdoor picnics or children parties. There is a big playground and garden and even a huge dog park across the road.

Medium sized park that's full of fun features for kids including a merry go round. The playground is huge! But it also gets crazy packed in the afternoon. Tons of elementary aged kiddos who also spill onto the grassy areas to run around and explore. We were lying on the grass and got smacked in the face by an errant soccer ball ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è. ‚Ä¶
This place was incredible, couldn‚Äôt imagine a more naturalistic place than these gardens. The park there is also profitable. Highly recommended! üëç ‚Ä¶

Relative to other gardens and parks in and around Paris this place is underwhelming. The use of "Jardin" seems to be a stretch as there is much much more grass than garden and plantings are few. It is in the middle of major, busy roads so it is a noisy area. Lots of benches to sit and eat your lunch as many locals come here to do. There is a puppet theatre, a children's playground, paths for walking and cycling, lots of grassy spaces for picnics. Unless you are nearby it's not worth the visit when there are so many more beautiful gardens to enjoy.
Everything was great. But the sittung needs to be tidied up once a while.

A nice park with many flat green areas and benches. There is several streets for cars within the park that makes it less of a calm area - you can easily hear the engines and the horns honking, as in the rest of Paris. There are areas to work out and also places for the kids to play. Garbage bins are easily accessible which is a great plus. All in all, nice park for a shorter stroll.
Great place for exercising and relaxing

Nice park in Paris 16. We stopped on the way to Bois de Boulogne. Love the water refill station near the entrance! Free entry to the park and there are free public toilets near the children's playground. Multi-sport areas here too. A good place for families.
Great place to sit on a blanket with friends to chat. A beautiful green space amid the city truly feels like nature is around us
A nice place to relax and have picnic with kids who will surely love to run and play around

Lovely park in the 16th arrondissement. There are several playgrounds for smaller children. The park is also good for walking dogs, although they have to wear a leash and preferably stay off the grass. Even the evening is buzzing with young people. It feels safe to walk there at anytime.
Very huge, beautiful park. Has multiple lawns and playgrounds, children's play area, and benches to both sit and have a picnic!! Relaxing and gem of a place.

An enormous park.  Park for the kids and adults. A store nearby if you need anything like food and drinks. Also a carousel to enjoy. Of course some materials for one to exercise.  So what more can you ask for for a park?  It's all in here! So visit this park and enjoy it for yourself...
Beautiful gardens. It will be gorgeous when the fountains are active...am sure  then it will rate 5 star status!
A unique garden. Great for kids.
Great for kids and super clean
Great park with children's play area and a public toilet. There is a sand area and water sprays for when the weather is hot.
Nice play area especially for the kids . Adults can have a long walk in & around this place in a silent environment
Lovely park
